---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Cocktails — Drink Terms That Score Big"
  description="Cocktail and drink words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. MARTINI (9pts), JULEP (14pts), WHISKY (18pts). Mixology vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble cocktail words, martini scrabble points, julep scrabble, whisky scrabble, drink words scrabble, mixology vocabulary scrabble, bar words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Cocktails — Drink Terms That Score Big","description":"Cocktail and drink words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. MARTINI (9pts), JULEP (14pts), WHISKY (18pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-cocktails"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is JULEP a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! JULEP scores 14 points (J=8, U=1, L=1, E=1, P=3). The J=8 tile makes this 5-letter cocktail name one of the highest-scoring drink words. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is WHISKY worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"WHISKY scores 18 points (W=4, H=4, I=1, S=1, K=5, Y=4). Three premium consonants (W=4, H=4, K=5) plus Y=4 make this 6-letter word a powerhouse scorer."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play MARTINI in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. MARTINI scores 9 points (M=3, A=1, R=1, T=1, I=1, N=1, I=1). A solid 7-letter bingo candidate — play all tiles from your rack for the 50-point bonus, totalling 59 points."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Cocktails — Drink Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">The cocktail bar is a goldmine for Scrabble players. Drink names pack premium consonants like J, K, W, and H — turning familiar bar vocabulary into surprisingly high-scoring plays.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WHISKY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JULEP</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MARTINI</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GIMLET</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Cocktail Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WHISKY — 18 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">W=4, H=4, I=1, S=1, K=5, Y=4 · 6 letters · Triple premium stack</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Four premium tiles in six letters. WHISKY stacks W=4, H=4, K=5, and Y=4 for 18 base points — that's 3.0 points per tile, exceptional for a natural English word without Q, X, or Z.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍸 JULEP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · J=8, U=1, L=1, E=1, P=3 · J power</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥃 WHISKY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · W=4, H=4, I=1, S=1, K=5, Y=4 · Quad premium</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍹 GIMLET</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · G=2, I=1, M=3, L=1, E=1, T=1 · 6 letters</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🍷 MARTINI</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · M=3, A=1, R=1, T=1, I=1, N=1, I=1 · Bingo</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Bar Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TODDY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PUNCH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STOUT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHAKER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BRANDY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MALT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Cocktail Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JULEP deploys J efficiently:</span> J=8 is the second-highest single tile. JULEP uses it in just 5 letters (2.8 pts/tile). When you draw the J, think mint julep — it's often your best J word at this length.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WHISKY stacks four premium tiles:</span> W+H+K+Y gives you 17 of the word's 18 points from just 4 tiles. This is rare density — look for it when you draw W and K together.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MARTINI is a sneaky bingo:</span> All common tiles (M, A, R, T, I, N, I) mean you'll draw this combination often. Hold for the 7-tile play — 59 total points beats any mid-rack dump.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Cocktail words excel because they contain <span class="text-white font-medium">premium consonant clusters</span>. W, H, K, and J appear frequently in drink names but rarely in everyday English — giving you an edge when these tiles land on your rack.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-food/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Food</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-desserts-bakery/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Desserts & Bakery</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid cocktail word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
